d on the NY NH and Canal Railroad. Made an assortment of mill gearing, pulleys, fan bellows, plow castings, and railing."},{"title":"Owner-operator of Glen Eyre PA","dates":"1869-?","type":"manufacturing","notes":"Moved to Glen Eyre, Pike County Pennsylvania in 1869 — engaged in the manufacture of furniture and in mercantile business, 'practically owning the whole town' per family history."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"From Northampton legislator to Pennsylvania town owner","body":"John Deming made farm implements in Northampton Massachusetts and served in the 1857 Massachusetts legislature. Returning to Farmington in 1858 he ran the Farmington Iron Foundry on the rail line, then in 1869 moved to Glen Eyre Pennsylvania, where furniture-making and mercantile business gave him ownership of 'practically the whole town.' He died in Brooklyn at sixty-eight."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909"},{"short":"Williams Family Genealogy","url":"http://dunhamwilcox.net/bios/williams.htm","notes":"The Williams Family — Rev. Joshua Williams + descendants."},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"},{"short":"Wilford Woodruff Papers — John Deming entry","url":"https://www.2023.wilfordwoodruffpapers.org/subjects/john-deming"},{"short":"Find a Grave — Riverside Cemetery Farmington CT","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/103605/riverside-cemetery"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"john-deming-1825"},"H02325":{"id":"H02325","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Catherine","middle_name":"Hooker","last_name":"Deming","maiden_name":"Williams","married_names":["Deming"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Catherine Hooker Williams Deming"},"birth":{"year":1826,"month":7,"day":26,"country":